FORUM: 44
POST: 91960
AUTHOR: 411847
DATE: 1357803600
BODY: 
Chrijm> Wow, that's some serious legacy code!  I think your smartest bet is to
add *specific* types to each .cpp file, like this,

    using std::string;
    using std::ostream;
    using std::cout;

There won't be too many. This approach is much cleaner than importing all of
the `std` namespace.
.
